books.title: Action Comics
books.generalCommentary: Graded 78 by the Sotheby's Grading Commitee in 1992. A copy stolen from actor Nic Cage

books.title: Marvel Comics
books.generalCommentary: Listed variously as "NM" and "VF". Was part of a 25,000 cash/trade deal in 1990. $115,000 trade listed in OS27. Was a 9.2

books.title: Marvel Comics
books.generalCommentary: OS 20 Trade data- $108,000. John Verzyl said that it was for $132,000. Either case its the earliest $100,000 comic, at least in terms of trade value. John did also verify the anecdote about this book. It is "perfect." There's nothing wrong with it. It's also supposedly got pretty nice registration.

books.title: Superman
books.generalCommentary: Best Existing. The "Dentist's" copy. Grade range is 8.0-9.2. What we do know is that he had the option to have both this and the Church copy in hand and went with this one.

sales.sellersNotes: Tony Arnold of TonyeTrade Enterprises, one of the renowned sources for vintage collectibles, and Roy Delic of Vintage Collectibles brokered the deal

books.title: Whiz
books.generalCommentary: Catalog NM+ Generally ranges from 9.0-9.8. OS 21 lists it as "MT." Changed hands in a cash/trade deal- $74,000 (1990)
